org.magnos.io
Interface Transferable<E>

Type Parameters:
E - The transferable object.
All Known Subinterfaces:
BufferFactory
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractBufferFactory, BufferFactoryBinary, BufferFactoryDirect, BufferFactoryFixed, BufferFactoryHeap, BufferFactoryMap
public interface Transferable<E>

A Transferable class is able to dump its collection of information into a list (by release) and then pass it to another Transferable which can take any acceptable pieces of that information and return a list of denied information (by transfer).

Author:
Philip Diffenderfer

A list of transferable elements.

transfer

java.util.List<E> transfer(java.util.List<E> elements)
Transfers all given elements into this class. This is the second step in transfering the elements from another Transferable into this class.

Parameters:

Returns:
